race.comment: UTILITARIAN (1) was a winner over this track and trip last time out, dropping out early before coming home with a powerful run to score by a long neck. Drops back in grade, so carries more weight but should prove tough to hold out. TIRITIRI (10) made considerable ground in the run home to finish third last start here. Carries a feather on his back and should be nearing his peak. Can play a major role. ZE BIRDS'N'ZEBEES (9) has two placings from three starts this prep and last start finished less than a length from the winner here. Peaking now and doesn't have to improve much to get the verdict. SUMADARTSON (4) hasn't won for quite some time but boasts peaks that measure up. Gets in well with the claim, though will just need some luck from the draw. JONQUEST (2) trialled well into his first-up run off 581 days but failed to make an impact. May need another run but is worth keeping an eye on.
